definition: to sprout/to come out (of seedling)/to bud

to go out/to come out/to occur/to produce/to go beyond/to rise/to put forth/to happen/(used after a verb to indicate an outward direction or a positive result)/classifier for dramas, plays, operas etc
Hmong or Miao ethnic group of southwest China/surname Miao

sentences.english: The rate of germinate of hole with plastic mulch was the highest.
sentences.chinese: 打孔覆膜栽培法的出苗率最高。

sentences.english: Sprout to mature for 90 days or so.
At present, reliable models about predicting weed germination are few.
sentences.chinese: 目前預測雜草的出苗的可靠模型還很少。

sentences.english: The fungicide treatment was useful for promoting the field emergence rate and the seedling quality.
sentences.chinese: 殺菌劑處理也提高了田間出苗率及幼苗素質。

sentences.english: Emergence percentage decreased as water contents decreased of as temperature increased or decreased.
sentences.chinese: 馬唐的日出苗率隨溫度的變化曲線大致呈鐘形。

sentences.english: Germination and emergence test was conducted on Eulaliopsis binata seeds stored for different time.
sentences.chinese: 用不同貯藏時間的龍鬚草種子做發芽和出苗試驗。

sentences.english: Early maturity, sprout to harvest 58 days.
The rate and evenness of emergence as well as production can be increased.
sentences.chinese: 提高了田間出苗率和整齊度，以及產量。

sentences.english: The treated seeds had a high rate of germination and almost germinated together.
sentences.chinese: 處理過的種子發芽率高且出苗一致。

sentences.english: Its application in germination rate of winter wheat was also studied.
sentences.chinese: 初步探討了其對冬麥種出苗率的影響。

sentences.english: Emergence does not only depend on soil temperature but also a function of variety.
sentences.chinese: 出苗不僅取決於土壤溫度，而且還取決品種的特點。

sentences.english: The rate of emergence was raised with disinfections of seed before the sowing.
sentences.chinese: 播種前進行種芋藥劑消毒可明顯提高出苗率。

sentences.english: To increase emergence days could lead to reduction of tuber yields.
sentences.chinese: 出苗天數的增加可導致塊莖產量大幅度減少。

sentences.english: There are very few crabs actually born in the lake.
sentences.chinese: 幾乎沒有什麼螃蟹是在陽澄湖裏出苗的。

definition: tiller (stem at the base of grass plants)
sowing in autumn (for a crop in spring)
to plant early/to sow seeds in early spring/early sowing
